news.title: Floods may prompt Karnataka government to reconsider Akrama-Sakrama
news.para: Unprecedented flooding and waterlogging in Bengaluru’s IT corridor may prompt the government to rethink plans of pushing the controversial Akrama-Sakrama scheme through. Many civil society members have revived demands to scrap the scheme altogether.

news.title: Highrises along Noida Expressway to get facade lights
news.para: The Noida Authority has changed the building bylaws to make facade lighting mandatory on these buildings. Advent Building, One Sky, Amity University and ATS Tower will get the lights in the first phase.

news.title: Greater Noida authority gives pre-2006 societies two years to get completion papers
news.para: This time extension was approved by the Greater Noida Board at its meeting in Lucknow on Friday, after it was informed that CCs could not be issued to some societies constructed in or before 2016 in Greater Noida due to lapse of time, officials said on Friday.

news.title: Indian Overseas Bank, Bank of Baroda raise MCLR rates by up to 0.10%
news.para: The benchmark 1-year tenor marginal cost of funds based lending rate (MCLR) has been revised to 7.75 per cent against the existing rate of 7.65 per cent.

news.title: Air India Group starts vacating its offices from government-owned properties
news.para: Airline staff in this office as also the ones in Delhi's Safdarjung Complex, GSD Complex and IGI Terminal One will be temporarily located in an office space in Gurugram beginning this month and will move to a newly-built Vatika complex in early 2023.

news.title: CCI dismisses JSW Paints' unfair business practice complaint against Asian Paints
news.para: ​​In an order dated September 8, the anti-trust regulator said no prima facie case of contravention of the provisions of either section 3 or 4 of the Competition Act is made out against Asian Paints.

news.title: Adani Group's open offer for ACC, Ambuja Cements gets mild response from investors
news.para: According to the afternoon updates, only 6.97 lakh shares of Ambuja Cements have been tendered in the escrow Demat account compared to the original offer for 51.63 crore shares from the public shareholders.

news.title: SC extends interim medical bail granted to ex-CMD of Amrapali group
news.para: "Perused the Interlocutory Application No. Issue notice on the application, returnable on September 23. Pending further consideration, the petitioner need not surrender in terms of the directions issued by this Court in its order dated August 8, 2022," the bench said in its order.

news.title: As housing market cools, homebuyers in USA regain leverage
news.para: An analysis of home sales data by Redfin shows that, on average, U.S. homes purchased during a four-week period in August sold for less than what sellers were asking. That hasn't happened since at least March 2021, according to the real estate brokerage.

news.title: Sunac China will oppose winding-up petition in Hong Kong
news.para: Sunac China is among a number of Chinese developers in Hong King, including China Evergrande Group, who have received similar petitions, with the region reeling under a wave of defaults in the debt-laden property market.

news.title: China Evergrande lenders appoint receiver to seize Hong Kong headquarters: Sources
news.para: Saddled with more than $300 billion in liabilities, Evergrande has been trying to sell its 26-storey China Evergrande Centre in Hong Kong's Wan Chai district after a potential $1.7 billion deal collapsed late last year, as part of the asset disposal effort to raise funds.

news.title: Punjab minister pulls up officials over illegal buildings in Ludhiana
news.para: The minister categorically asked about few buildings against which he had received complaints. The officials concerned claimed that they had already served notices to the owners of the buildings.

news.title: Allow sand mining at fixed sites, says South Goa MP
news.para: He demanded that the sand extraction by traditional methods be permitted with restrictions such as not being carried out in the vicinity of bunds or bridges.

news.title: NGT issues notice to Rajasthan government over pollution by brick kilns
news.para: National Green Tribunal (NGT) central zone bench Bhopal issued notice to the state government on a petition over pollution caused by brick kilns using coal. The next hearing of the case is on October 18.

news.title: Find cost of 870 trees cut for MLAs housing project: Orissa HC
news.para: The order came on a PIL filed by Cuttack-based social activist Jayanti Das against the cutting of trees for the Rs 549. 41-crore MLA Colony project in the capital.
